s play in helping to put future Olympic champions on the path to Games glory really tug at the emotional heartstrings and are capable of turning even the most cynical viewers into emotional wrecks.\", \"from\": 6082, \"to\": 6328, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The company's incredible tributes\", \"from\": 6082, \"to\": 6115}, {\"ngram\": \"the role\", \"from\": 6119, \"to\": 6127}, {\"ngram\": \"mums\", \"from\": 6128, \"to\": 6132}, {\"ngram\": \"future Olympic champions\", \"from\": 6156, \"to\": 6180}, {\"ngram\": \"the path\", \"from\": 6184, \"to\": 6192}, {\"ngram\": \"Games glory\", \"from\": 6196, \"to\": 6207}, {\"ngram\": \"really tug\", \"from\": 6208, \"to\": 6218}, {\"ngram\": \"the emotional heartstrings\", \"from\": 6222, \"to\": 6248}, {\"ngram\": \"even the most cynical viewers\", \"from\": 6276, \"to\": 6305}, {\"ngram\": \"emotional wrecks\", \"from\": 6311, \"to\": 6327}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Pick Them Back Up' is a worthy gold winner, generating some of the most intense feelings of positivity we have ever seen for an ad.\\\"\", \"from\": 6330, \"to\": 6463, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a worthy gold winner\", \"from\": 6353, \"to\": 6373}, {\"ngram\": \"the most intense feelings\", \"from\": 6394, \"to\": 6419}, {\"ngram\": \"positivity\", \"from\": 6423, \"to\": 6433}, {\"ngram\": \"an ad\", \"from\": 6456, \"to\": 6461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He added, \\\"It's also great to see Channel 4's sensational campaign, 'We are The Superhumans' in the top 6.\", \"from\": 6465, \"to\": 6571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6499, \"end\": 6508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channel_4\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6148861439746663e-17, \"text\": \"Channel 4\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channel_4\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Channel_4\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Superhumans\", \"from\": 6541, \"to\": 6556}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Generating incredibly intense feelings of inspiration, the ad has played a crucial role in putting the Paralympics firmly in the hearts and minds of viewers all around the world.\\\"\", \"from\": 6572, \"to\": 6751, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"incredibly intense feelings\", \"from\": 6583, \"to\": 6610}, {\"ngram\": \"inspiration\", \"from\": 6614, \"to\": 6625}, {\"ngram\": \"the ad\", \"from\": 6627, \"to\": 6633}, {\"ngram\": \"a crucial role\", \"from\": 6645, \"to\": 6659}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympics\", \"from\": 6671, \"to\": 6686}, {\"ngram\": \"the hearts\", \"from\": 6697, \"to\": 6707}, {\"ngram\": \"minds\", \"from\": 6712, \"to\": 6717}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 6721, \"to\": 6728}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 6740, \"to\": 6749}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What can I add?\", \"from\": 6753, \"to\": 6768, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have known Forrester since September 2012, when he joined the Unruly Group as global insight lead.\", \"from\": 6770, \"to\": 6870, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Forrester\", \"from\": 6783, \"to\": 6792}, {\"ngram\": \"September\", \"from\": 6799, \"to\": 6808}, {\"ngram\": \"the Unruly Group\", \"from\": 6830, \"to\": 6846}, {\"ngram\": \"global insight lead\", \"from\": 6850, \"to\": 6869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And I talked with him several times over the next six years about Unruly's Viral Spiral charts, which showed which video ads were among the most shared.\", \"from\": 6871, \"to\": 7023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6952, \"end\": 6958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spiral\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8925289882210302e-21, \"text\": \"Spiral\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spiral\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spiral\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the next six years\", \"from\": 6912, \"to\": 6930}, {\"ngram\": \"which video ads\", \"from\": 6980, \"to\": 6995}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, I have learned that Forrester has the kind ofExperience, Expertise, Authoritativeness, and Trustworthiness (E-E-A-T)that not only Google talks about, but skeptical journalists and bloggers value, too.\", \"from\": 7025, \"to\": 7229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7120, \"end\": 7135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_(social_science)\", \"score\": 0.9989539615314192, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Trustworthiness\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_(social_science)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trust_(social_science)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Forrester\", \"from\": 7049, \"to\": 7058}, {\"ngram\": \"the kind ofExperience\", \"from\": 7063, \"to\": 7084}, {\"ngram\": \"Expertise\", \"from\": 7086, \"to\": 7095}, {\"ngram\": \"Authoritativeness\", \"from\": 7097, \"to\": 7114}, {\"ngram\": \"E\", \"from\": 7137, \"to\": 7138}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's why I have quoted him - along with other video gurus - in articles like \\\"What's The Alternative To Spending $7 Million On A Super Bowl Ad?\\\"\", \"from\": 7231, \"to\": 7377, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other video gurus\", \"from\": 7273, \"to\": 7290}, {\"ngram\": \"articles\", \"from\": 7296, \"to\": 7304}, {\"ngram\": \"The Alternative\", \"from\": 7318, \"to\": 7333}, {\"ngram\": \"A Super Bowl Ad\", \"from\": 7360, \"to\": 7375}]}, {\"sentence\": \"as well as \\\"How To Make A Video Go Viral.\\\"\", \"from\": 7378, \"to\": 7420, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A Video\", \"from\": 7402, \"to\": 7409}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's why I have cited DAIVID's critical data and strategic insights in articles like \\\"The Best 5 Super Bowl Ads in 2024 (Brands That Got It Right)\\\" as well as \\\"39 Emotions Digital Marketers Can Use In Advertising.\\\"\", \"from\": 7422, \"to\": 7642, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"DAIVID's critical data\", \"from\": 7450, \"to\": 7472}, {\"ngram\": \"strategic insights\", \"from\": 7477, \"to\": 7495}, {\"ngram\": \"articles\", \"from\": 7499, \"to\": 7507}, {\"ngram\": \"The Best 5 Super Bowl Ads\", \"from\": 7514, \"to\": 7539}, {\"ngram\": \"(Brands\", \"from\": 7548, \"to\": 7555}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"39 Emotions Digital Marketers\", \"from\": 7587, \"to\": 7617}, {\"ngram\": \"Advertising\", \"from\": 7629, \"to\": 7640}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But if you want to figure out what P&G already understands, then it's worth spending a few moments learning more about DAIVID's methodology.\", \"from\": 7644, \"to\": 7784, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7679, \"end\": 7682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a few moments\", \"from\": 7729, \"to\": 7742}, {\"ngram\": \"DAIVID's methodology\", \"from\": 7763, \"to\": 7783}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Based in London, DAIVID leverages technologies like facial coding, eye tracking, and computer vision to help advertisers enhance the emotional and business impact of their campaigns.\", \"from\": 7786, \"to\": 7968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7795, \"end\": 7801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.3803121864097555e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"DAIVID leverages technologies\", \"from\": 7803, \"to\": 7832}, {\"ngram\": \"facial coding\", \"from\": 7838, \"to\": 7851}, {\"ngram\": \"eye tracking\", \"from\": 7853, \"to\": 7865}, {\"ngram\": \"computer vision\", \"from\": 7871, \"to\": 7886}, {\"ngram\": \"advertisers\", \"from\": 7895, \"to\": 7906}, {\"ngram\": \"the emotional and business impact\", \"from\": 7915, \"to\": 7948}, {\"ngram\": \"their campaigns\", \"from\": 7952, \"to\": 7967}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their platform allows marketers to assess and improve ad effectiveness on a large scale using advanced data analysis methods.\", \"from\": 7970, \"to\": 8095, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their platform\", \"from\": 7970, \"to\": 7984}, {\"ngram\": \"marketers\", \"from\": 7992, \"to\": 8001}, {\"ngram\": \"ad effectiveness\", \"from\": 8024, \"to\": 8040}, {\"ngram\": \"a large scale\", \"from\": 8044, \"to\": 8057}, {\"ngram\": \"advanced data analysis methods\", \"from\": 8064, \"to\": 8094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"DAIVID's study of the most emotionally engaging Olympics ads utilized its Self-Serve solution, trained on millions of consumer data points, to predict the emotional reactions and attention levels ads would generate, along with their potential brand and business impacts.\", \"from\": 8097, \"to\": 8367, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"DAIVID's study\", \"from\": 8097, \"to\": 8111}, {\"ngram\": \"the most emotionally engaging Olympics ads\", \"from\": 8115, \"to\": 8157}, {\"ngram\": \"its Self-Serve solution\", \"from\": 8167, \"to\": 8190}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 8203, \"to\": 8211}, {\"ngram\": \"consumer data points\", \"from\": 8215, \"to\": 8235}, {\"ngram\": \"the emotional reactions\", \"from\": 8248, \"to\": 8271}, {\"ngram\": \"attention levels ads\", \"from\": 8276, \"to\": 8296}, {\"ngram\": \"their potential brand and business impacts\", \"from\": 8324, \"to\": 8366}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The analysis involved 56 Olympic ads, excluding those from the current Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 8369, \"to\": 8455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8440, \"end\": 8454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The analysis\", \"from\": 8369, \"to\": 8381}, {\"ngram\": \"56 Olympic ads\", \"from\": 8391, \"to\": 8405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the Paris Olympics has progressed, all released advertisements were uploaded to DAIVID's platform through its API.\", \"from\": 8457, \"to\": 8574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8464, \"end\": 8478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 8570, \"end\": 8573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/API\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0047183405272669e-13, \"text\": \"API\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/API\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/API\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"advertisements\", \"from\": 8508, \"to\": 8522}, {\"ngram\": \"DAIVID's platform\", \"from\": 8540, \"to\": 8557}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The platform's predictive AI then evaluated and ranked the ads based on the anticipated strength of positive emotions they would evoke.\", \"from\": 8575, \"to\": 8710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8601, \"end\": 8603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.831760392842409e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ads\", \"from\": 8630, \"to\": 8637}, {\"ngram\": \"the anticipated strength\", \"from\": 8647, \"to\": 8671}, {\"ngram\": \"positive emotions\", \"from\": 8675, \"to\": 8692}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In total, 47 ads were analyzed in the study.\", \"from\": 8711, \"to\": 8755, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"total\", \"from\": 8714, \"to\": 8719}, {\"ngram\": \"47 ads\", \"from\": 8721, \"to\": 8727}, {\"ngram\": \"the study\", \"from\": 8745, \"to\": 8754}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, watch the 10 ads above and see for yourself what kind of video content triggers intense positive emotions in viewers.\", \"from\": 8757, \"to\": 8878, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 10 ads\", \"from\": 8767, \"to\": 8777}, {\"ngram\": \"what kind\", \"from\": 8805, \"to\": 8814}, {\"ngram\": \"video content\", \"from\": 8818, \"to\": 8831}, {\"ngram\": \"intense positive emotions\", \"from\": 8841, \"to\": 8866}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 8870, \"to\": 8877}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You may see something that I might have missed.\", \"from\": 8879, \"to\": 8926, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 8891, \"to\": 8900}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Past performance is no guarantee of future results as P&G found out after not having a mention at the Paris Olympics, despite having 5 ads in the top 7 of all time.\", \"from\": 8928, \"to\": 9092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8982, \"end\": 8985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Past performance\", \"from\": 8928, \"to\": 8944}, {\"ngram\": \"no guarantee\", \"from\": 8948, \"to\": 8960}, {\"ngram\": \"future results\", \"from\": 8964, \"to\": 8978}, {\"ngram\": \"a mention\", \"from\": 9013, \"to\": 9022}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 9026, \"to\": 9044}, {\"ngram\": \"5 ads\", \"from\": 9061, \"to\": 9066}, {\"ngram\": \"all time\", \"from\": 9083, \"to\": 9091}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Next time you want to know if your ad creative is working, test it.\", \"from\": 9094, \"to\": 9161, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your ad\", \"from\": 9124, \"to\": 9131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"P&G take note.\", \"from\": 9162, \"to\": 9176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9162, \"end\": 9165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"P&G\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Procter_&_Gamble\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"note\", \"from\": 9171, \"to\": 9175}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I know, talking about testing social videos the way that Madison Avenue once tested TV commercials seems like pie in the sky.\", \"from\": 9178, \"to\": 9303, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"social videos\", \"from\": 9208, \"to\": 9221}, {\"ngram\": \"Madison Avenue\", \"from\": 9235, \"to\": 9249}, {\"ngram\": \"TV commercials\", \"from\": 9262, \"to\": 9276}, {\"ngram\": \"pie\", \"from\": 9288, \"to\": 9291}, {\"ngram\": \"the sky\", \"from\": 9295, \"to\": 9302}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Does that guarantee future success?\", \"from\": 9305, \"to\": 9340, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"future success\", \"from\": 9325, \"to\": 9339}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, AI can not be creative like humans can.\", \"from\": 9341, \"to\": 9386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9347, \"end\": 9349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.831760392842409e-16, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"humans\", \"from\": 9375, \"to\": 9381}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, the heart of every great video is still innovative, surprising, human-led creativity.\", \"from\": 9388, \"to\": 9477, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 9392, \"to\": 9401}, {\"ngram\": \"every great video\", \"from\": 9405, \"to\": 9422}, {\"ngram\": \"innovative, surprising,